DAT
id=qid::label=str::text=lstr::
664::$$$message_0003_0000_0000$$$::There's a respectable dojo built within the Emiya house.[lr]::
665::$$$message_0003_0000_0001$$$::It was added as an afterthought when the entire house was being built.[lr]::
666::$$$message_0003_0000_0002$$$::It was nothing more than a hobby and indulgence.::
667::$$$message_0003_0001_0000$$$::"Okay, then."[lr]::
668::$$$message_0003_0001_0001$$$::I'll do some light exercise before breakfast.[lr]::
669::$$$message_0003_0001_0002$$$::I'm not really studying martial arts, but my old man once told me,[lr]::
670::$$$message_0003_0001_0003$$$::"If you want to be like me, you'll need to harden your body."[r]::
671::$$$message_0003_0001_0004$$$::Since then, I've made a point of working out every day.::
672::$$$message_0003_0002_0000$$$::"Ninety-nine...one hundred."[lr]::
673::$$$message_0003_0002_0001$$$::I finish my daily sit-ups and change from my dougi into my school uniform.[lr]::
674::$$$message_0003_0002_0002$$$::Since I overslept, I decide to work out just enough to satisfy me.[lr]::
675::$$$message_0003_0002_0003$$$::A few sit-ups with no stretching should be enough.[lr]::
676::$$$message_0003_0002_0004$$$::I'm not built to bulk up, and no matter how important they say body building is, it's not like I want to get into fights.::
677::$$$message_0003_0003_0000$$$::All I need is to gain enough athletic ability to handle unexpected situations, and be able to move the way my silly ideals require.[lr]::
678::$$$message_0003_0003_0001$$$::After all, the thing I most want to be is the complete opposite of an athlete.::
679::$$$message_0003_0004_0000$$$::"...Oh. It's getting late."[lr]::
680::$$$message_0003_0004_0001$$$::I toss my sweaty dougi in the laundry hamper.[lr]::
681::$$$message_0003_0004_0002$$$::It's already twenty past six.[lr]::
682::$$$message_0003_0004_0003$$$::The Emiya household's mornings start early, so even this time would be considered late for breakfast.::
683::$$$message_0003_0005_0000$$$::Breakfast is already prepared.[lr]::
684::$$$message_0003_0005_0001$$$::The appetizing scent of the breakfast Sakura cooked wafts toward me from the dining table.::
685::$$$message_0003_0006_0000$$$::"You must have had a good workout. Breakfast is ready."[lr]::
686::$$$message_0003_0006_0001$$$::"Oh...thanks. Sorry I made you work more because I overslept."::
687::$$$message_0003_0007_0000$$$::"It's no trouble. And you did not oversleep. You're not in any school clubs, so it's still early."::
688::$$$message_0003_0008_0000$$$::"Clubs have nothing to do with it. And if they do, you coming by in the mornings must be a lot of trouble since you do have morning practice."[lr]::
689::$$$message_0003_0008_0001$$$::"Oh...well, I want to do this, so please don't worry about me."::
690::$$$message_0003_0009_0000$$$::"Yeah. You keep telling me that, which is why I wake up early, club or no.[lr]::
691::$$$message_0003_0009_0001$$$::If you're coming by, it'd be rude to still be asleep."::
692::$$$message_0003_0010_0000$$$::To me, waking up early is waking up before Sakura gets here, and oversleeping means I make Sakura prepare breakfast on her own, like today.::
693::$$$message_0003_0011_0000$$$::"Teehee. You really are a stickler about this kind of thing. Even Mitsuzuri-senpai says you're honest to a fault and annoying, even though you're so crude."[lr]::
694::$$$message_0003_0011_0001$$$::Mitsuzuri is the captain of the kyudou club Sakura is in, and she and I seem to cross paths often.::
695::$$$message_0003_0012_0000$$$::"Hm. Is she still griping about me to you?"[lr]::
696::$$$message_0003_0012_0001$$$::"Yes. She's working hard every day to bring you to your knees with her archery skills before you graduate."::
697::$$$message_0003_0013_0000$$$::"Is that so? She must be better than me by now. You know how memories get glorified. I don't mind the reverence, but I guess that depends on who sees me that way, too."[lr]::
698::$$$message_0003_0013_0001$$$::"Mitsuzuri-senpai is really competitive. I'm sure she sees you as competition."::
699::$$$message_0003_0014_0000$$$::Sakura scoops rice into a bowl as she talks.[lr]::
700::$$$message_0003_0014_0001$$$::It's almost six thirty.[lr]::
701::$$$message_0003_0014_0002$$$::The kyudou club's morning practice starts at seven.[lr]::
702::$$$message_0003_0014_0003$$$::Attendance is not mandatory, but she doesn't have much time left.::
703::$$$message_0003_0015_0000$$$::"Fuji-nee...should be here soon. Well, it's her fault for not being here on time. Sakura, let's go ahead and start eating."[lr]::
704::$$$message_0003_0015_0001$$$::"You're right. Here you go, Senpai."[lr]::
705::$$$message_0003_0015_0002$$$::Sakura hands me the rice bowl with a smile.[lr]::
706::$$$message_0003_0015_0003$$$::"...Ack."[lr]::
707::$$$message_0003_0015_0004$$$::Oops.[lr]::
708::$$$message_0003_0015_0005$$$::I should be used to this every morning, but her delicate fingers catch my attention.::
709::$$$message_0003_0016_0000$$$::"...!"[lr]::
710::$$$message_0003_0016_0001$$$::...I can't explain it, but it's awkward.[lr]::
711::$$$message_0003_0016_0002$$$::I'm not sure if it's our age, but Sakura's been looking more provocative lately.[lr]::
712::$$$message_0003_0016_0003$$$::Her casual movements are so pretty, she often takes my breath away.[lr]::
713::$$$message_0003_0016_0004$$$::Maybe it's because I never saw Sakura that way before, but now I'm noticing how feminine she's becoming. ::
714::$$$message_0003_0017_0000$$$::"Senpai? Is something the matter?"[lr]::
715::$$$message_0003_0017_0001$$$::"No, it's nothing. Don't worry about it."[lr]::
716::$$$message_0003_0017_0002$$$::"Hm?"[lr]::
717::$$$message_0003_0017_0003$$$::...Honestly, it's baffling.[lr]::
718::$$$message_0003_0017_0004$$$::Why the hell am I getting nervous around my friend's younger sister?[lr]::
719::$$$message_0003_0017_0005$$$::Sakura's just a really good and considerate younger friend of mine, and she's someone I need to look after.::
720::$$$message_0003_0018_0000$$$::She's the younger sister of a friend of mine. We used to be friendly, though initially we weren't very close since she's a grade below me.::
721::$$$message_0003_0019_0000$$$::It was only a year and a half ago that our relationship became more what it is now.[lr]::
722::$$$message_0003_0019_0001$$$::Sakura started to come and cook meals for me when I got hurt, and things kind of stayed like that.::
723::$$$message_0003_0020_0000$$$::I think this arrangement was supposed to last until I got better, but I guess something or other happened, and somehow she ended up helping out with household chores.::
724::$$$message_0003_0021_0000$$$::Either way, Sakura's a good cook, and her cleaning and laundry skills are perfect.[lr]::
725::$$$message_0003_0021_0001$$$::Having her come early in the morning is a big help. But it's been disconcerting recently.[lr]::
726::$$$message_0003_0021_0002$$$::Sakura isn't the problem. It's me.::
727::$$$message_0003_0022_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
728::$$$message_0003_0022_0001$$$::I'm sure being flustered by my friend's sister is part of the reason I feel guilty. [lr]::
729::$$$message_0003_0022_0002$$$::Usually I'm unphased, but when I blush because I get caught off guard like now, I wonder whether that's problematic as her senpai.::

